<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1819-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1819-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                            <head>
                                <seg type="margin">[121]</seg>
                                <hi rend="italic">*Mr. <persName type="from">Adams</persName>,
                                    Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Glenn</persName>,
                                    district attorney.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1819-05-11"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 11,
                                1819</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your letter of the 8th
                                instant. Mr. Biscoe, inspector of the customs at Nottingham, will
                                deliver you this letter. He goes to Baltimore in pursuit of the
                                Irresistible, which after having been seized by the officers at
                                Nottingham was taken from them, and is supposed to be at
                                Baltimore.</p>
                            <p>I beg leave once more to recommend this vessel to your particular
                                attention, and that you will use every legal exertion to bring to
                                justice those who have made her the instrument of their
                                piracies.</p>
                            <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>JOHN Q. ADAMS.</signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Elias Glenn</hi>, Esq.</p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>